generate(root) compiles the program in one call under the rules in lang/code, and generate(root, node, baseline) regenerates it under lang/code plus lang/reduce with that node dropped and the baseline handed back to the model as the thing it is correcting, and both of them read the answer as the last fenced python block whose fences each stand alone on their own line, because the compiler's own source carries fences inside its string literals and a fence found in the middle of a line is not a fence, and both send an unparseable answer back to the model with the parser's exact error appended, twice, before failing loudly, since nothing here may ever swallow a SyntaxError or accept an answer that carried no python at all;
